intro: Sagraea woodsii, commonly known as the Florida star jasmine, is a flowering plant native to the southeastern United States. It is a member of the Oleaceae family and is characterized by its fragrant, star-shaped white flowers. The plant typically grows as a shrub or small tree, reaching heights of up to 15 feet. Its leaves are opposite, simple, and have a glossy, dark green appearance. Sagraea woodsii thrives in well-drained soil and is often found in wetlands, hammocks, and along waterways.
